      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to clinical hemolysis endpoints; relative hemolysis index RH is the primary regulatory metric.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and derived relative hemolysis index (RH). Both are directly cited in FDA guidance for CPB device submissions and map to plasma-free hemoglobin endpoints in clinical use."
