      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters traceable to measurement data or published sources; inlet boundary conditions documented with uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow waveforms sourced from the CPB inlet boundary condition dataset (dataVintage 2025-10-10). Blood analog viscosity and density from ISO 10993-4 reference values. The dataset was collected approximately three weeks before the November 2025 model revision that introduced updated near-wall turbulence treatment. The assessment team determined this revision did not alter the physical interpretation of the inlet boundary conditions — which are imposed upstream of the near-wall region — and therefore characterized the dataset as remaining applicable without re-collection. No formal sensitivity analysis was performed to quantify the effect of the turbulence model change on the inlet BC requirements."
    },
